TextSection.Contents: Complete septate uterus is a rare non-syndromic uterovaginal malformation characterized by a uterus that has a longitudinal septum which elongates from the uterine fundus to the internal or external cervical os. Most often women are asymptomatic however dysmenorrhea unilateral obstruction and endometriosis could be observed. Unlike urinary tract abnormalities which are very rarely associated poor reproductive outcome is frequent.
